# Fork-only sys/ helper sources — the DB9/SNAC/Saturn/key-gate HDL that does
# NOT exist in MiSTer-devel upstream. One basename per line; blank lines and
# `#` comments ignored.
#
# Single source of truth for two consumers (kept here so they can't drift):
#   * setup_cicd.sh — the SYS_HELPERS propagation loop that cp's these from
#     fork_ci_template/sys/ into each ported fork's sys/.
#   * rerere_train.sh::assert_fork_helpers_unchanged — the post-merge guard.
#     Upstream carries none of these, so any upstream-merge diff on them is a
#     rerere mis-replay (the 00f49da class: a stale unstable-canary resolution
#     replayed pre-feature text and reverted joydb.sv); the guard aborts.
#
# Symlinked into fork_ci_template/.github/sys_helpers.list so `cp -rL`
# materialises it next to the propagated rerere_train.sh in every fork.
joydb9md.v
joydb15.v
joydb9saturn.v
joydb.sv
joydb_remap.sv
siphash24.v
db9_key_gate.sv
db9_key_secret.vh
